      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Boom pacer KEAYANG RENEGADE (6) stretched his unbeaten run to four when he came from one spot wider and raced parked before cruising home by 9.5m at this circuit and distance last week. Has plenty of upside and can continue to work through his grades. SANCHEZ (12) was a class above at Ballarat last start, coming from this row and working before scoring by 5m. Has been producing good results in strong company this time. Could threaten if things go his way from a tricky draw. LOUGLE (13) is another drawn wide on the back row but his form is hard to knock having made it four wins on the trot by scoring from this row here last week. That took his record at this distance to five wins and a placing from six attempts. Player. MAAS BETTING AGAIN (3) comes up against some handy rivals but draws nicely and is going well having put two wins together.",
